                  <p class="card-img-heading">
                    &lt;/spider&gt; Web Designing
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div class="card-inner">
                  <section class="content-inner">
                    <h2 class="content-sub-heading">
                      &lt;/spider&gt; Web Designing
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                      <a class="btn collapsed waves-attach waves-button"
                      data-toggle="collapse" href=
                      "cs#collapsible-region-4"><span class=
											"collapsed-hide"><i class="fa fa-eye-slash"></i> hide</span><span class=
											"collapsed-show"><i class="fa fa-eye"></i> view</span></a>
                    </p>
                    <div class="collapsible-region collapse" id=
                    "collapsible-region-4">
                      <div>
                        <p id="rules">
                          Rules
                        </p>1. Registration is allowed as an Individual or as a
                        Team of 2 members.<br>
                        2. Certificate of participation will be issued to each
                        participant.<br>
                        3. Participants will be given a problem statement on
                        the spot for which you will have to develop a
                        functional website.<br>
                        4. Participants will have approximately 3 hours to
                        design and develop your website.<br>
                        5. All the required tools will be given to you on the
                        day of the competition.<br>
                        6. The website must be developed using HTML, CSS,
                        JavaScript and JQuery.<br>
                        7. Participants will not be allowed to carry any of
                        their personal softwares, flash drives, CDs, DVDs or
                        any other accessories.<br>
                        8. You will not be allowed to take back any of the
                        complete/incomplete product.<br>
                        9. Prelims will be conducted depending upon the number
                        of participants.<br>
                        10. In any case, the decision of the judges will be
                        final.<br>
                        11. Directions provided by the coordinators should be
                        strictly adhered to.<br>
                        Development Tools and Materials<br>
                        1. Google Chrome<br>
                        2. Mozilla Firefox<br>
                        3. Adobe Photoshop<br>
                        4. jQuery 1.11.3<br>
                        5. jQuery UI 1.11.4<br>
                        6. CSS Handbook<br>
                        7. Bootstrap Framework<br>
                        8. Foundation Framework<br>
                        9. Few content like images, icon packs, etc. will be
                        provided to each participant.<br>
                        10. Sublime Text<br>
                        Prelims round<br>
                        1. The round will consist of questions that will
                        challenge the web designing skills of the
                        participants.<br>
                        2. The round will be of 30 minutes in duration.<br>
                        3. Participants will be tabbed for the Main round on
                        the basis of the relative performance in the Prelims
                        round.<br>
                        4. Marks of the prelims will not be carried forward to
                        the next round.<br>
                        Mains round<br>
                        1. This is the round of actual web designing.<br>
                        2. You have to Design a website on the provided
                        problem. Problem will be revealed in the Mains
                        round.<br>
                        3. The above mentioned development tools and materials
                        will be provided.<br>
                        4. The participants will have to do a two minute oral
                        presentation on submission of project to the
                        judges.<br>
                        Judging Criteria<br>
                        1. Content.<br>
                        2. Aesthetics.<br>
                        3. Design.<br>
                        4. Usability and accessibility.<br>
                        5. Code conventions
                        <p></p>
                        <p></p>
